      "issue": "No distributed tracing and no stuck-order gauge metric make incident diagnosis unacceptably slow",
      "reason": "Without tracing, the on-call engineer cannot determine root cause across service boundaries during an active incident. Without a stuck-order gauge, they cannot answer 'how many orders are affected right now' — the most basic incident scoping question. Estimated time-to-diagnosis increases from 2-5 minutes (with tracing) to 15-30 minutes (manual log correlation). For an order processing system, that delay directly translates to revenue impact and customer harm.",
      "routed_to": "Coach K"
